Ubi Franklin’s fourth baby mama, Sandra Iheuwa, has tackled a troll who said she was always pregnant. The businesswoman who is expecting a child with her estranged husband, Steve Thompson, Royal Hairs boss shared a video and some photos of her sparingly unclad self, dancing and rocking her baby bump. Reacting to the post, an unidentified social media user wrote: “This lady is always pregnant. Mother of many nation(s).”   You’re number one star maker, Nkechi Blessing hails Mercy…     The bible inaccurate, unreliable – Dancehall artiste…     Annie Idibia begs 2baba for a decade of faithfulness   With the comment not sitting well with the expectant mother, she challenged her critic to also try getting pregnant if it was that easy while highlighting the age gap between her children. She replied: “@edwardbrown7701 how am I always pregnant? If you may know, my first child is 13 years old, the second is 7 years old and the third child is 3 years old. so, how am I always pregnant? “Y’all will read rubbish online and run with it…..and if it’s easy to be pregnant, try it. Take your negativity off my page.”